/// anthropic_llm.urchin — forward declaration of an externally
/// implemented handler. design sketch.
///
/// extern handlers are the bridge to the host language. at runtime
/// start, the engine looks for a Rust impl registered under the name
/// `AnthropicLlm` to fulfill io.llm. all real-world IO (HTTP, the LLM
/// APIs, the filesystem, audio, sensors) lives here — anything the
/// Urchin interpreter can't and shouldn't implement itself.
///
/// no body: the implementation isn't in Urchin. the file is the
/// contract that says "this handler exists; trust the runtime to
/// resolve it."

extern handler AnthropicLlm for io.llm
